WEBVTT

00:01.877 --> 00:03.962
Ten seconds!
Ooh. Alright.

00:03.962 --> 00:05.214
[ "Action News" theme song
plays ]

00:05.214 --> 00:06.798
Ooh.

00:06.798 --> 00:07.799
Ah.

00:07.799 --> 00:09.134
Oh, we love "Action News".

00:09.134 --> 00:10.719
We get in early
just to watch it.

00:10.719 --> 00:13.096
It just calms you down after
wanting to take a wrench

00:13.096 --> 00:15.349
to someone's side mirror
in traffic.

00:15.349 --> 00:17.976
But the Philadelphia region
continues to suffer

00:17.976 --> 00:20.020
temperatures in the mid‐90s

00:20.020 --> 00:21.813
with the heat index approaching
100...

00:21.813 --> 00:23.899
Now, I'm a proud, married,
Christian woman,

00:23.899 --> 00:25.817
and I love my husband.

00:25.817 --> 00:28.487
But there's something about
that Jim Gardner.

00:28.487 --> 00:31.740
That non‐regional diction.

00:31.740 --> 00:33.283
We haven't seen anything
like this...

00:33.283 --> 00:35.202
Jacob: It is so important
to support and acknowledge

00:35.202 --> 00:37.829
local journalism, okay?
There's no agenda here.

00:37.829 --> 00:40.707
This is ‐‐ This is on
the ground, in the streets,

00:40.707 --> 00:42.668
powerful stuff.

00:42.668 --> 00:44.586
Barbara: [ Laughs ]

00:44.586 --> 00:46.380
Wouldn't want to see that dog
in traffic.
Yes, Jim.

00:46.380 --> 00:48.465
I like the news,
because that's when I can say

00:48.465 --> 00:53.971
whatever I want
and nobody asks any questions.

00:53.971 --> 00:56.598
Taking a personal day.
Going fishing with my friends.

00:56.598 --> 00:59.393
Anyways, toilet paper's
in the closet.

00:59.393 --> 01:02.813
I saw Jim Gardner once,
at the Chipotle.

01:02.813 --> 01:06.525
Ooh, he ordered a bowl
so handsomely.

01:09.528 --> 01:17.995
♪♪

01:19.121 --> 01:21.331
[Rapping] ♪ I be in and
out of town with my bros ♪

01:21.331 --> 01:22.708
♪ Still wylin' on
these hoes ♪

01:22.708 --> 01:24.209
♪ They the cons,
we the pros ♪

01:24.209 --> 01:27.212
Tariq, oh, my God.
That's ‐‐ That's it.
That's a little sample.

01:27.212 --> 01:29.339
That is so good. And you
recorded that last night?

01:29.339 --> 01:31.049
Yeah, yeah.
Did it in like 15 minutes.

01:31.049 --> 01:32.134
It's nothing.
Wow.

01:32.134 --> 01:33.218
Yeah. Super fast.
Wow.

01:33.218 --> 01:35.762
Tariq is my boyfriend
of over 10 years,

01:35.762 --> 01:38.557
and he's been a music artist
since we were in high school.

01:38.557 --> 01:40.642
Clearly, he's very, very good.

01:40.642 --> 01:42.603
Um, all of his TikToks go viral,

01:42.603 --> 01:45.605
which nowadays, is the true mark
of a great musician.

01:45.605 --> 01:48.483
I'll be home kinda late tonight
'cause I got a show.

01:48.483 --> 01:50.319
I sold out
the King's Lounge.

01:50.319 --> 01:51.361
Stop.
Yeah.

01:51.361 --> 01:52.529
Oh, my goodness!
Yeah.

01:52.529 --> 01:53.947
I'm so proud of you!
Thank you.

01:53.947 --> 01:55.615
Maybe I could come.
Oh, no, no, no.

01:55.615 --> 01:57.701
You can't come, 'cause they got
a strict capacity thing.

01:57.701 --> 01:59.703
And it's 15 people.
Oh.

01:59.703 --> 02:01.038
So if you come,
then it's 16,

02:01.038 --> 02:04.166
and then it's a fire hazard,
and then they shut it down.

02:04.166 --> 02:06.251
But look.
You wanna do dinner tonight?

02:06.251 --> 02:09.338
I'll be home around 10.
I'll bring you Bahama Breeze.

02:09.338 --> 02:10.756
That is my favorite.
I know. I know.

02:10.756 --> 02:12.174
That's my favorite! Okay.
I know. Yeah.

02:12.174 --> 02:13.592
Alright.
Alright, baby.

02:13.592 --> 02:14.885
Alright.

02:14.885 --> 02:16.219
Ooh, you got that seat
far up!

02:16.219 --> 02:18.013
You know I'm short.
Damn. Okay. Ahh.

02:18.013 --> 02:19.681
Alright, baby,
I gotta get goin'.

02:19.681 --> 02:21.850
I'm hungry as hell,
and although it is that hunger

02:21.850 --> 02:23.894
that keeps me going,
I gotta eat something.

02:23.894 --> 02:25.937
Okay. Well, why don't you just
take my breakfast sandwich?

02:25.937 --> 02:27.773
Huh?
Yeah. I'll get
something at school.

02:27.773 --> 02:29.274
Are you sure, baby?
Yeah. I'll get
something in there.

02:29.274 --> 02:31.234
Oh, thank you so much.
You're welcome.

02:31.234 --> 02:32.402
I love you.
I love you, too.

02:32.402 --> 02:34.071
Yeah.

02:34.071 --> 02:36.615
Um, look, we didn't get to
discuss this last night

02:36.615 --> 02:38.784
because you were
making the hits, but...

02:38.784 --> 02:41.119
our rent is going up,
so we need to redo the budget.

02:41.119 --> 02:42.746
Mm‐hmm. Mm‐hmm.
I left that, uh,

02:42.746 --> 02:44.331
bill‐organizer thing
on the fridge.

02:44.331 --> 02:46.124
Mm‐hmm. Yeah.
I'll get to it.
Okay.

02:46.124 --> 02:48.043
Yeah, but, no, I was just
thinking, like, you'd get to it

02:48.043 --> 02:50.295
kind of soon because
my name's on the lease

02:50.295 --> 02:52.381
and we were already
late on rent once.

02:52.381 --> 02:54.716
Oh, I got you, baby. Can we
talk about it later, though?

02:54.716 --> 02:56.093
It's not even 8:00
in the morning, and you know

02:56.093 --> 02:58.261
I don't even wake up till, like,
noon o'clock in the morning.

02:58.261 --> 03:00.597
Yeah. Could you just
look at it, though, you think?

03:00.597 --> 03:04.476
I'll get to it.
I promise, baby.

03:04.476 --> 03:05.519
Okay.
Okay?

03:05.519 --> 03:06.603
Alright.
I love you.

03:06.603 --> 03:07.896
Love you, too.
Thanks for the sandwich.

03:07.896 --> 03:09.314
Have a good one.
You're welcome.

03:09.314 --> 03:12.693
Mmm.
[ Breathes deeply ]

03:12.693 --> 03:14.319
[ Lights buzzing ]

03:14.319 --> 03:16.697
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:19.700 --> 03:21.785
Melina, what's wrong?

03:21.785 --> 03:24.830
I don't want to walk down
the hallway, Ms. Janine.

03:24.830 --> 03:26.498
It's scary.

03:26.498 --> 03:28.792
I don't want
to go to school.

03:28.792 --> 03:30.627
What ‐‐ Hey, Mr. Johnson.

03:30.627 --> 03:32.629
These lights have been
going on and off for weeks.

03:32.629 --> 03:34.172
Are you gonna do
anything about them?

03:34.172 --> 03:35.590
The kids don't even
wanna walk in.

03:35.590 --> 03:37.259
Mr. Johnson:
Above my pay grade, Janine.

03:37.259 --> 03:38.802
I make most
electrical things work

03:38.802 --> 03:41.596
with a makeshift system
I've had since '92.

03:41.596 --> 03:44.266
For this, we gotta wait
on an electrician.

03:44.266 --> 03:46.184
But ‐‐
Goin' fishin'.

03:46.184 --> 03:47.477
I'll get to it.

03:47.477 --> 03:51.022
[ Sighs ]
Don't worry, Melina.

03:51.022 --> 03:52.983
I actually am going to
get to it,

03:52.983 --> 03:54.860
unlike janitors
and boyfriends.

03:54.860 --> 03:56.153
Huh?

03:56.153 --> 03:58.363
Just ‐‐ Come on.

03:58.363 --> 03:59.698
Whose branzino is this?

03:59.698 --> 04:02.492
That is a very powerfully
smelling fish

04:02.492 --> 04:04.911
to put in a shared fridge.
Don't touch it.

04:04.911 --> 04:06.997
I'm making it tonight
at my cousin Annette's.

04:06.997 --> 04:08.748
She thinks she's
the best cook in the family.

04:08.748 --> 04:11.001
I'm gonna show her
in a nonthreatening way.

04:11.001 --> 04:13.003
I'm‐a look cuter
than her, too.

04:13.003 --> 04:15.839
Guys, the lights in the back
hallway have been out for weeks.

04:15.839 --> 04:17.716
‐Thank you for the update.
‐What are you wearing?

04:17.716 --> 04:20.802
And we need to do something
about it. Okay?

04:20.802 --> 04:22.637
Uh, uh, Melina,
from your class ‐‐

04:22.637 --> 04:24.389
yeah, she was afraid to come
to school this morning.

04:24.389 --> 04:25.974
Said it looked like
"The Shining,"

04:25.974 --> 04:27.809
and I don't even get
how she knows that reference.

04:27.809 --> 04:29.561
‐She loves "The Shining."
‐It's a classic movie.

04:29.561 --> 04:31.688
This isn't okay, alright? And
I already talked to Mr. Johnson,

04:31.688 --> 04:33.356
and he said there isn't
anything he can do.

04:33.356 --> 04:35.025
What do you want us
to do about it?

04:35.025 --> 04:37.694
It can't be hard. It's just
screwing in a few new bulbs.

04:37.694 --> 04:42.365
Janine, just worry about
what can be controlled.

04:42.365 --> 04:45.035
Exactly. All we can do
on a hot day like this

04:45.035 --> 04:46.578
is our own jobs, anyway.

04:46.578 --> 04:48.705
I know that's right!
Why is it February

04:48.705 --> 04:50.624
and hotter than the devil's
booty‐hole outside?

04:50.624 --> 04:52.167
Climate change.

04:52.167 --> 04:54.085
We are living in the middle
of its disastrous effects.

04:54.085 --> 04:55.420
The permafrost in Russia ‐‐

04:55.420 --> 04:57.088
[ Coughs ] Nerd.
[ Coughs ]

04:57.088 --> 04:58.507
[ Laughing ]

04:58.507 --> 05:00.383
Ava, can someone
from the city

05:00.383 --> 05:02.010
come and check on
the back‐hallway lights?

05:02.010 --> 05:04.679
Girl, no. Do I look like
the Kool‐Aid Man?

05:04.679 --> 05:06.348
I don't have enough juice
to manipulate

05:06.348 --> 05:07.682
the inner workings
of city hall.

05:07.682 --> 05:09.184
[ Bell rings ]

05:09.184 --> 05:10.852
Ava: They'll probably
come in the summer.

05:10.852 --> 05:13.146
In the summer?
Jacob: Tough break.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.065
Want some egg‐white bites?

05:15.065 --> 05:18.068
No.
I don't have time to eat.

05:18.068 --> 05:21.071
They're just egg‐white bites.
You microwave them.

05:21.071 --> 05:24.407
See, I just
can't accept this.

05:24.407 --> 05:26.618
You know, they didn't see
those kids' faces.

05:26.618 --> 05:29.830
It was like they walked into
The Haunted Mansion at Disney,

05:29.830 --> 05:32.249
which is a very scary ride,
by the way.

05:32.249 --> 05:33.917
I don't care what people say.

05:33.917 --> 05:36.586
Okay, so, we went over the days
of the week. Now we ‐‐

05:36.586 --> 05:38.713
[ Door opens ]
Alright, baby, sit down.

05:38.713 --> 05:40.799
Um...it's 9:00.

05:40.799 --> 05:42.717
Word.

05:45.136 --> 05:49.266
Uh, school starts
earlier than...that.

05:49.266 --> 05:50.725
Look, I know
you're just a sub,

05:50.725 --> 05:52.811
but these kids need to be
in their seats by 8:00.

05:52.811 --> 05:54.729
It's a school requirement.
Understood.

05:54.729 --> 05:56.439
Sixth time in two weeks
that kid's been late.

05:56.439 --> 05:58.984
Seems like a drop in a bucket,
but then...

05:58.984 --> 06:02.070
that bucket overflows
and everything gets sticky.

06:03.154 --> 06:04.948
We don't want to get sticky,
do we?

06:07.367 --> 06:09.619
Y'all are getting this, right?!

06:09.619 --> 06:11.663
[ Lights buzzing ]

06:12.664 --> 06:14.249
[ Humming ]

06:17.919 --> 06:19.921
[ Clears throat ]

06:19.921 --> 06:22.799
Oh, um, hey, Mrs. Howard,
can I get some advice?

06:22.799 --> 06:25.635
I was gonna ask Janine,
but she seems busy.

06:25.635 --> 06:28.680
‐Oh, sure. Come on in.
‐Thanks.

06:30.807 --> 06:32.392
‐Okay.
‐Have a seat.

06:33.602 --> 06:35.437
Mm‐hmm.

06:35.437 --> 06:36.938
Y‐Yeah. Yeah.

06:42.485 --> 06:45.030
So, one of my students
has been coming in late ‐‐

06:45.030 --> 06:47.407
9:00, to be exact ‐‐
for the last week or so.

06:47.407 --> 06:48.992
Did you talk
to the parent?

06:48.992 --> 06:50.827
No. No. I'm a sub.
I don't want to be

06:50.827 --> 06:52.829
mixing it up with parents.
It's unnecessary.

06:52.829 --> 06:54.581
Sweetheart,
this isn't happy hour.

06:54.581 --> 06:56.541
You are the child's teacher.

06:56.541 --> 06:58.793
Which child is it?
Uh, Williams.

06:58.793 --> 07:00.295
Um, Joel Williams.

07:00.295 --> 07:02.672
Okay. I know that family.
[ Bell rings ]

07:02.672 --> 07:05.550
Oh, listen, I've got to go
pick my kids up from the gym,

07:05.550 --> 07:08.887
so why don't you meet me
during my free time,

07:08.887 --> 07:11.681
which is my nail appointment
during lunch.

07:11.681 --> 07:15.518
Um, I was gonna eat in my car.
I brought a sandwich from home.

07:15.518 --> 07:18.396
Okay. Then bring your little
Nissan sandwich with you.

07:20.523 --> 07:23.026
Janine: The more senior teachers
are just used to giving in,

07:23.026 --> 07:25.528
but I, however,
am young, sprightly,

07:25.528 --> 07:28.073
and know where
they keep the ladder.

07:28.073 --> 07:30.116
Forgot I was afraid of ladders.

07:30.116 --> 07:31.743
[ Ladder creaking ]

07:31.743 --> 07:34.245
[ Lights buzzing ]

07:34.245 --> 07:35.455
[ Panel clatters ]

07:35.455 --> 07:36.790
[ Stomach gurgles ]

07:36.790 --> 07:39.167
[ Chuckles ]
That was just my stomach.

07:39.167 --> 07:40.877
Okay.

07:40.877 --> 07:43.171
Oh. Oh, look at this.

07:43.171 --> 07:45.340
It was just a loose wire.

07:45.340 --> 07:48.176
[ Buzzing ]

07:48.176 --> 07:50.387
[ Buzzing intensifies ]

07:50.387 --> 07:52.597
[ Zapping ]
Ooh!

07:52.597 --> 07:54.140
[ Gasps ]

07:56.976 --> 07:59.354
Oh, God. Can someone
please help me down?

07:59.354 --> 08:01.606
And why would we do
that, since you clearly
caused this situation?

08:01.606 --> 08:04.651
Okay. I didn't know
doing this would cause
all the power to go out.

08:04.651 --> 08:06.444
Well, the power
is not all out.

08:06.444 --> 08:08.780
It's on in some places
and off in others.

08:08.780 --> 08:10.657
‐It's off in my room.
‐On in the gym.

08:10.657 --> 08:12.283
Yeah, it's off
in my room.

08:12.283 --> 08:15.203
Thank God we got the A/C,
or we'd all be meltin' already.

08:15.203 --> 08:17.664
Okay, best thing to do
in these situations is
just stay calm and ‐‐

08:17.664 --> 08:19.916
Okay! This is it, y'all!
The end times!

08:19.916 --> 08:21.835
It's three months early,
but it's happening!

08:21.835 --> 08:23.586
Aah!
Don't shake the ladder!

08:23.586 --> 08:26.840
Gregory is the only person
that can stay in my bunker,
so stop asking.

08:26.840 --> 08:28.925
Hell yeah,
I'm a doomsday prepper.

08:28.925 --> 08:30.301
[ Scoffs ]
Why wouldn't I be?

08:30.301 --> 08:32.095
I don't know why
more people aren't.

08:32.095 --> 08:34.681
Have you seen "Train to Busan"?
With the fast‐ass zombies?

08:34.681 --> 08:38.977
[ Scoffs ] That day is coming.
That day soon come.

08:38.977 --> 08:42.272
Ava, it is just
a partial power outage.

08:42.272 --> 08:43.815
Alright.
Listen up, everybody ‐‐

08:43.815 --> 08:45.650
‐Listen to Barbara, y'all!
‐Are you kidding me?

08:45.650 --> 08:47.068
This is what
we're gonna do ‐‐

08:47.068 --> 08:48.820
everybody without power,
please, head to the gym.

08:48.820 --> 08:50.947
‐Head.
‐We will conduct classes there

08:50.947 --> 08:52.824
until this is all fixed.

08:52.824 --> 08:55.535
It is not ideal,
but it will work.

08:55.535 --> 08:57.162
You heard her.
Let's go.

08:57.162 --> 08:59.205
Guys ‐‐ Guys, I‐I just want to
say, I‐I'm sorry, everybody.

08:59.205 --> 09:01.166
I just thought if I could
get up here and get this done,

09:01.166 --> 09:02.542
then we wouldn't
have to wait and...

09:02.542 --> 09:04.085
And look where it landed us,
baby girl.

09:04.085 --> 09:05.670
Yeah, how'd that
work out for you?

09:05.670 --> 09:07.255
Everybody, please,
head to the gym.

09:07.255 --> 09:09.382
We've got bigger fish
to fry now.

09:09.382 --> 09:11.009
Oh, Jesus! My branzino!

09:11.009 --> 09:12.677
Everybody out of the way!
Out of the way!

09:12.677 --> 09:14.179
If someone
could please help me?

09:14.179 --> 09:16.014
I feel like I'm one wobble away
from death.

09:16.014 --> 09:17.766
A‐Alright. Okay.
I got you.

09:17.766 --> 09:19.350
‐Okay. Hi. Thank you.
‐We good.

09:19.350 --> 09:20.852
Give me your hand.
Take your time.

09:20.852 --> 09:22.145
‐Okay.
‐Whenever you're ready.

09:22.145 --> 09:24.606
‐Okay. Am I doing it?
‐No.

09:24.606 --> 09:26.149
‐Let's go to a count of three.
‐Okay.

09:26.149 --> 09:28.193
One, two...

09:28.193 --> 09:29.527
three.

09:29.527 --> 09:30.862
One more time.

09:30.862 --> 09:33.573
And it's pointing
to the number...

09:33.573 --> 09:35.116
Right here. Thank you.
Four!

09:35.116 --> 09:36.201
Turn ‐‐ Turn around.

09:36.201 --> 09:38.661
This is all my fault.
[ Buzzer buzzes ]

09:38.661 --> 09:40.205
Yeah, you probably shouldn't
have tried to do the job

09:40.205 --> 09:43.208
of a newly graduated DeVry
student, but this is okay.

09:43.208 --> 09:45.043
[ Cellphone chimes ]

09:45.043 --> 09:46.336
[ Janine sighs ]

09:46.336 --> 09:48.296
[ Cellphone chimes ]

09:53.343 --> 09:56.096
I made this mess,
and I need to fix this.

09:56.096 --> 09:57.430
Okay, but fix this how?

09:57.430 --> 09:59.057
It seems very outside
of your skill set.

09:59.057 --> 10:00.725
You should probably just wait
for somebody to get to it ‐‐

10:00.725 --> 10:02.936
I don't want to wait
for someone to get to it.

10:02.936 --> 10:06.648
You know, our children have
needs that deserve to be met.

10:06.648 --> 10:08.900
And I'm going to fix this.

10:08.900 --> 10:10.568
Nothing is going to
get in my way.

10:10.568 --> 10:12.362
What if you have to
climb another ladder?

10:12.362 --> 10:14.364
Those seem very tricky
for you.

10:14.364 --> 10:17.784
No. Not today.

10:17.784 --> 10:18.827
[ Bell rings ]

10:18.827 --> 10:20.578
Aren't you going
to lunch, Janine?

10:20.578 --> 10:23.373
Uh, no. I'm gonna stay and help
the lunch ladies with lunch.

10:23.373 --> 10:25.125
The lunch ladies
don't like you.

10:25.125 --> 10:29.129
She always coming in the kitchen
saying "hello" and whatnot.

10:29.129 --> 10:31.131
It's unsanitary.

10:31.131 --> 10:32.715
Is that what
you're really doing?

10:32.715 --> 10:36.010
Yes! And maybe trying
to get the lights back on.

10:36.010 --> 10:37.887
Would you give that a rest?
What do you want?

10:37.887 --> 10:39.347
To make the whole school
blow up?

10:39.347 --> 10:41.641
No. Plus, I can't.

10:41.641 --> 10:44.310
Luckily, the school was built as
a bomb shelter in World War II,

10:44.310 --> 10:45.937
so...

10:45.937 --> 10:47.647
Let it go.

10:49.482 --> 10:51.359
Okay. I will.

10:56.614 --> 10:58.366
You're not gonna let it go,
are you?

10:58.366 --> 11:00.493
No, I'm not gonna let it go,
Jacob, okay?

11:00.493 --> 11:02.120
I need to right my wrong.

11:02.120 --> 11:04.789
Okay.
Well, count me out.

11:04.789 --> 11:06.040
I never counted you in.

11:06.040 --> 11:07.333
Well, then count me in,

11:07.333 --> 11:09.919
because I don't have
any lunch plans.

11:09.919 --> 11:12.422
Okay. Come on.

11:12.422 --> 11:13.506
Okay.

11:14.632 --> 11:16.676
Hi. Can I help you?

11:16.676 --> 11:18.803
Oh, I'm just here
to talk to her.

11:18.803 --> 11:20.555
You need your nails done
to sit.

11:20.555 --> 11:22.307
What color
are you doing?

11:22.307 --> 11:24.475
Um...clear?

11:24.475 --> 11:26.019
No loitering
and no clear.

11:26.019 --> 11:29.564
